# Design System Integration

Use project design tokens and components consistently. Avoid hardcoding values.

## Component Usage

- **IMPORTANT**: Always use components from `@/shared/components` when possible.
- **Button**: `Button` from `@/shared/components/button` — variants: `primary`, `secondary`, `outline`, `ghost`, `destructive`.
- **Card**: `Card`, `CardHeader`, `CardTitle`, `CardContent`, `CardFooter` from `@/shared/components/card`.
- **Modal**: `Modal` from `@/shared/components/modal`.
- Place new shared UI in `src/shared/components/[component-name]/` with `index.tsx`.
- Feature-specific UI goes in `src/features/[feature]/components/[component-name]/`.

## Design Tokens (No Hardcoding)

All tokens live in `src/app/globals.css` via `@theme`. Use these, never raw hex or arbitrary values:

| Category | Use | Avoid |
|----------|-----|-------|
| **Colors** | `bg-surface`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`, `text-primary-600`, `text-success`, `text-error`, `text-warning` | `bg-white`, `text-black`, `#3b82f6` |
| **Typography** | `text-display`, `text-heading`, `text-body`, `text-caption`, `text-mono` | Arbitrary `text-[14px]`, `font-[500]` |
| **Spacing** | `p-4`, `gap-6`, `rounded-lg` (theme `--border-radius`) | `p-[13px]`, `rounded-[7px]` |
| **Component classes** | `dashboard-card`, `metric-card`, `status-badge`, `input`, `tab-button` | Repeating long class strings |

## Icons & Assets

- Icons: `src/assets/icons/` — export in `src/assets/icons/index.ts`. Use: `import { CloseIcon } from '@/assets/icons';`
- Logos: `src/assets/logos/` — reference via path or Next.js `Image`.
- **DO NOT** add new icon packages. Use Figma-provided assets or existing project icons.
- Use `cn()` from `@/shared/utils/cn` for merging `className`.

## Accessibility

- Follow WCAG: labels for inputs, `alt` for images, `aria-label` for icon-only buttons.
- Use semantic HTML and focus states (`focus:ring-2 focus:ring-ring`).

## Layout Primitives

- Flex: `flex`, `flex-col`, `items-center`, `justify-between`, `gap-4`.
- Grid: `grid`, `grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4`, `gap-6`.
- Mobile-first: base styles for mobile, then `md:`, `lg:` for larger screens.
